#+title: Carbohydrates
#+author: Paul Gerald D. Pare
#+date: August 26, 2023

* Definition
- biomolecules made up of carbon, hydrogen and oxygen.
- Examples include: Sugar, starches, fiber
- always found on the exterior of the cell membrane.
* Functions
- forms distinctive cellular markers & Cell-to-cell recognition.
  + Important in _organ & tissue_ development
- Cell-pathogen interaction
  + It is the basis for rejection of foreign cells by *immune system*
* Types
:PROPERTIES:
:ID:       14c51f19-c712-4fb3-933c-cc6629a202e7
:END:
** Glycoproteins
:PROPERTIES:
:ID:       64350c8c-86e0-4f48-ad12-56df2bd5fd0b
:END:
- attached to proteins
** Glycolipids
:PROPERTIES:
:ID:       7bff25d9-807a-4214-a1da-aa2965a012fd
:END:
- attached to lipids
** Glycocalyx
:PROPERTIES:
:ID:       9198cbc3-fca4-4d8b-bf7b-1b14e6bc508d
:END:
- _highly hydrophilic_
- mixture of glycoprotein and glycolipid
  + to prevent the entry of pathogens into the cell.
